            <p>Gold has been valued for its beauty, durability, and rarity. Here are some key points:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Purity:</strong> Measured in karats, with 24K being pure gold.</li>
                <li><strong>Uses:</strong> Jewelry, electronics, and investment.</li>
                <li><strong>Care:</strong> Clean regularly to maintain shine.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Silver</h3>
            <p>Silver is versatile and affordable. Key points:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Purity:</strong> Sterling silver is 92.5% pure.</li>
                <li><strong>Uses:</strong> Jewelry, cutlery, and industry.</li>
                <li><strong>Care:</strong> Polish regularly to prevent tarnishing.</li>
            </ul>
